<HEADLINE> Iraq Beats Uzbekistan in Nehru Gold Cup Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Iraq beat Uzbekistan 6-1 in the
preliminary league match of the five-nation Nehru Gold Cup
international soccer tournament in Chochin, India, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Iraq led the first half 2-0 through Hayder Majeed, who scored
in the 14th minute, and Sadiq Abdul Ridha who had a goal in the
36th.
</P>
<P>
Iraq enlarged the margin by adding four goals in the second
half, where Ridha scored in the 57th minute.
</P>
<P>
The other three Iraqi goals came from Laith Shihab in the 52nd
minute, Hayder Abdullah in the 86th and Sarah Khalif in the 88th.
</P>
<P>
Uzbekistan's sole goal was scored by Mataliev Ravshanjon in the
69th minute. 
</P>
