<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Leader Meets Norwegian Storting President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OSLO, April 2 (xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing
Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC), said
here today that there is no fundamental conflict of interest
between China and Norway and China is willing to enhance
consultation and cooperation with Norway.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, who arrived here this morning for a four-day official
visit to Norway, made the remarks when meeting with Kirti
Grondahl, President of the Norwegian Storting (parliament).
</P>
<P>
He said that Norway was one of the first Western countries to
establish diplomatic ties with China and the two countries have
identical views on major issues.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral cooperation and exchanges in various fields have
developed rapidly since the two countries established diplomatic
ties 40 years ago, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that President Jiang Zemin's state visit to Norway last
year pushed the bilateral relationship to a new stage and the
Chinese government and people look forward to the visit to China
by King Harald V.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that despite their different history and cultural
tradition, China and Norway can forge a long-term and stable
relationship of friendship and cooperation oriented to the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
Grondahl hoped that the Norwegian Storting and the Chinese NPC
would further enhance their cooperation and exchanges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
