<HEADLINE> German Delegation to Visit Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A high-powered German delegation
arrives in Harare next month for a round of talks with Zimbabwean
businessmen and also attends a major summit to drum up support
for the region's investment drive.
</P>
<P>
German Ambassador to Zimbabwe Norwin Graf Leutrum today said,
''we are expecting a delegation of between 20 and 25 business
persons to visit Zimbabwe from May 19 to 24 to meet their local
counterparts and also attend the World Economic Forum Summit,''
Leutrum said.
</P>
<P>
The envoy said the delegation would include companies
interested in investing in the agro-industrial, manufacturing,
mining and tourism sectors, which are said by economists to be
the key to Zimbabwe's economic revival in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Leutrum said Germany, Zimbabwe's third largest trading partner
after South Africa and Britain, is keen to increase investment
and further consolidate existing bilateral economic and political
relations.
</P>
<P>
He said bilateral trade between the two countries continued to
increase every year and now exceeded 118 million U.S. Dollars,
although Zimbabwe enjoys a healthy trade balance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
