<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Set up New Anti-Drug Body </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam will set up an anti-drug
police department to fight the growing drug abuses and trafficking
in the country, an official report said today.
</P>
<P>
The new department will assist the police chief in directing
the fight against drug-related crimes and ensuring security and
social order.
</P>
<P>
Anti-narcotics police handled more than 3,800 drug trafficking
cases in 1996 and arrested 6,650 people for drug-related
offenses. But drug trafficking and abuses are still on the rise.
</P>
<P>
There are about 140,000 drug addicts nationwide, according to a
national anti-drug program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
