<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seminar on Angolan Environment, City Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A seminar on Angola's environment
management and city governing opened here today with the theme
centering on how to work out the national policy on environment
and priority development of the cities.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening session, Secretary of State on
Environment David Mendes said besides, it needs to confirm what
function the central government, local authorities, mass
organizations and private departments have in managing city
environment and administering basic service infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from 10 Angolan provinces are attending the
three-day seminar to formulate environment strategy on the
cities, and discuss the environment situation in the country and
the reconstruction of its cities after the civil war.
</P>
<P>
It will also elaborate on the experience of Mozambique and
Cape Verde in environment management, and on reconstruction
programs of Angola's cities, especially Lobito and Benguela in
the central part with 46.7 million U.S. Dollars funded by the
World Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
