<HEADLINE> German Industrialists Probe Investment Chances in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A team of German industrialists
arrived here today to probe the investment potentials here.
</P>
<P>
"We are interested in investing in the fields of civil
engineering, foodstuff industry, tourism and transport," Rudolf
Bronkhorst, leader of the delegation said on arrival in the
airport here.
</P>
<P>
He noted that "we hope to acquaint ourselves with Mozambique's
policy toward foreign investment, its preferential measures and
the road and transport situation in the country."
</P>
<P>
Diaete Krohnert, a team member, declared, "we are fully ready
to provide Mozambique with fund, technology and equipment."
</P>
<P>
During its week-long stay in the country, the Germans will
have talks with Oldemiro Baloi, Minister of Industry, Trade and
Tourism, and officials from the Investment Promoting Center and
the Chamber of Commerce on how best to invest in this country.
</P>
<P>
So far, Portugal, South Africa and Britain have the lion's
part of the foreign investment in Mozambique which amounts to 1.5
billion U.S. Dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
