<BODY>
<HEADLINE> All Farm Products Increase in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean agricultural produce
had recorded high growth in 1996, Agriculture Minister Dennis
Norman said here today in a wide-ranging policy statement.
</P>
<P>
He said maize production went up from an estimated 839,000
tons in 1995 to 2,609,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Seed cotton production increased from 106,000 tons to 275,000
tons, wheat went up from 65,000 tons to 250,000 tons, while
tobacco rose from 198,000 tons to an estimated 209,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
''Similar trends were experienced with most of the other
crops,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
The outlook for the current season is good, with most areas
having received more than 100 percent of their normal rainfall
and over 50 percent of the dams now full, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
