<HEADLINE> Chinese Government Delegation Arrives in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese government delegation
led by Vice Premier of the State Council Jiang Chunyun arrived in
Uganda today for a five-day official visit to the east African
country.
</P>
<P>
The 20-member delegation was received at the Entebbe
International Airport near here by Ugandan State Minister for
Foreign Affairs in Charge of International Cooperation Rebecca
Kadaga.
</P>
<P>
In his writen speech on arrival at the airport, Jiang said
that during his visit he will exchange views with leaders of
Uganda on the bilateral relations and international regional
issues of common interest with a view to enhancing mutual
understanding, promoting Sino-Ugandan freindly cooperation and
gaining more knowledge about the achievements the Ugandan people
have made in various areas.
</P>
<P>
He said his visit will contribute to the further enhancement
of trust and friendship between China and Uganda, consolidate and
strengthen the existing friendly cooperation between the two
countries and further promote the solidarity and cooperation
between them.
</P>
<P>
Uganda is the third stop on his current African trip which has
already taken him to Mauritius and Madagascar and will carry him on
to Algeria. enditem

