<HEADLINE> Turkey, Slovakia Sign Cooperation Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Turkey and Slovakia today signed
four agreements in the fields of cooperation on economy, air
transportation and environment protection.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed here during Slovakian Prime Minister
Vladamir Meciar's three-day visit starting today.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan also had a meeting
with Merciar. Erbakan said their talks were "extremely
productive," adding that Turkey and Slovakia would help each other
in the international field.
</P>
<P>
Erbakan expressed his hope that the existing cooperation
should be expanded between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Before their talks, Erbakan said an improved Turkey-Slovakia
relationship "will not only contribute to peoples of the two
states, but also to the Balkans, whole Europe and the world."
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that there exists a great potential in
commercial ties, cooperation in the fields of tourism and defense
and in joint investments between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Meciar said that Slovakia and Turkey had similar
views on the issues of the new security system and economic order
in Europe.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters upon his arrival at Ankara that "a new page
will be opened in Turkish-Slovakian ties" through his visit.
</P>
<P>
"Slovakia has positive dialog with Turkey since the state of
Slovakia was established in 1993," said he, adding, "our dialog
has been improving every year as there exists no problem between
the two countries." 
</P>
</TEXT>
