<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spring Blizzard Hitting Northeastern Region in US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A sudden spring blizzard dropped
as much as three feet of snow on northeastern parts of the United
States between March 31 and April 1, causing havoc there, local
media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The snow and high winds sent trees and power lines crashing to
the ground throughout the northern parts of three states of New
York, New Jersey and Connecticut.
</P>
<P>
In Connecticut, almost 100,000 households had lost electricity
by noon on Monday. Another 100,000 homes lost power in New Jersey.
Officials said that it would take until Thursday to restore power
to everyone.
</P>
<P>
Major roads were closed Monday night and Tuesday morning in New
York, New Jersey and Connecticut. 
</P>
</TEXT>
