<HEADLINE> Killer of Pupils Sentenced to Death in Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Sanaa Court of Appeal today
sentenced Hassan Ali al-Baadani to death for random shooting which
killed eight people and injured 11 others last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Having heard the sentence, the accused appealed, demanding that
his case be referred to the Supreme Court.
</P>
<P>
Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh Tuesday denounced the
shooting incident while visiting the victims in the Thawra public
hospital.
</P>
<P>
The victims include a number of pupils, two school teachers
and several citizens.
</P>
<P>
President Saleh has also issued a directive to grant families
of the victims sums of money as well as the treatment of the
injured at state expense, including the ones who will require
treatment abroad. 
