<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Leader on China-Norway Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oslo, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese National People's Congress
(NPC) Chairman Qiao Shi said today that China and Norway each have
their own economic advantages and there is a great potential for
continued development of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a dinner given in his honor by Norwegian Storting
President Kirsti Grondahl, he said that the two countries have
identical or similar views on major international issues.
</P>
<P>
China has all along held that countries, regardless of their
size, are equal members of the international community, he said,
with the joint efforts of both sides, Sino-Norwegian friendly
relations and cooperation based on mutual respect, equality and
mutual benefit will undoubtedly witness greater development.
</P>
<P>
He also indicated that the Chinese government and people look
forward to the visit to China by His Majesty King Harald V and Her
Majesty the Queen in October this year.
</P>
<P>
"We are convinced that the visit will undoubtedly further
strengthen the friendly relations and cooperation between China
and Norway," he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, President Grondahl said that the Norwegian people
are interested in China's development and China's development is
of great importance not only to China itself but also to the
world.
</P>
<P>
Norway is willing to develop its friendly relations and
cooperation with China in various fields, she added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Qiao Shi also met with members of the Foreign Affairs
Committee of the Norwegian Storting and exchanged views with them
on China's democracy and legal system, as well as other issues of
mutual interest.  
</P>
</TEXT>
