<HEADLINE> EU Special Meeting on Mideast to Be Held Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) special
meeting on the Middle East situation, required by France, will be
held on Monday next week in Brussels, the spokesman of the French
foreign ministry Yves Doutriaux said today.
</P>
<P>
The political directors of the foreign ministry of 15 EU
countries will join the meeting, which will focus on the grave
situation in the Palestinian territory following the Israeli
decision to build a new Jewish settlement in Har Homa district of
East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The French foreign ministry spokesman said that the meeting
will allow EU countries to reach a consensus on the relaunching of
the peace process in the Middle East, which he said has now
entered an impasse.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman again expressed the deep concern of France over
the violence which is taking place on a daily basis in the
Palestinian territory.
</P>
<P>
He said that the indispensable way for re-establishing
confidence between Israel and Palestinians is to suspend the
construction of the Har Homa settlement, and a resumption of talks
between Israel and Palestinians on all issues, including the
withdrawal of Israeli troops from the West Bank. 
</P>
