<HEADLINE> Private Sector Capital Rises in Addis Ababa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Addis Ababa Regional Trade,
Industry and Tourism Bureau said today the capital of the private
sector has shown an increase of 15.2 billion birr (6.643 birr
equal one US Dollar) over the past four years.
</P>
<P>
The capital was less than 2 billion birr four years ago, the
bureau said, adding that the boom was mainly due to the new
economic policy and the mashrooming of joint stock companies.
</P>
<P>
According to the bureau, the private industrial sector capital
has grown to 8.7 billion birr from the initial 1.1 billion birr
in the past four years.
</P>
<P>
The aggregate capital of companies engaged in the
non-industrial sector has grown from 500 million birr to 7.1
billion birr while that of individual businessmen increased to
1.4 billion birr from the initial 300 million birr during the
same period. enditem

