<HEADLINE> 3 Million Nigerians Suffer from Diabetes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 2 (Xinhua) -- About three million people in Nigeria
suffer from diabetes, accounting for 2.5 percent of the estimated
total figure of 120 million in the world, experts said here today.
</P>
<P>
This means that about three percent of the 115 million
Nigerians suffer from the disease.
</P>
<P>
According to the Lagos State Chapter of Dabetes Association of
Nigeria (DAN), the number of sufferers in the West African country has
doubled to the present figure over the past decade.
</P>
<P>
The high incidence of diabetes in the country is attributed to
ignorance and poverty, DAN officials said.
</P>
<P>
The association has been making efforts to educate and assist the
less privileged in the country, they said.  
</P>
