<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Rehabilitates 3 Hydro-Electric Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Electric Light
and Power Authority said today the rehabilitation of three hydro
electric power stations is well underway at a cost of
61 million Birr (about 9.2 million U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The authority said the 100-megawatt Fincha station, which went
into operation 25 years ago, is currently under reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
New machines are being installed at the station at a cost of
13 million Birr (about 1.9 million Dollars) from the government
of Norway, the authority said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the other two power stations, the
authority said the production capacity of Koka power station
which was 43.2 megawatts at the outset of its establishment 35
years ago, has now declined to 25 megawatts.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the capability of the Tis Abay power station, set
up about 32 years ago, has reduced by more than half from the
initial 11.4 megawatts.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government will allot 48 million Birr
(about 7.2 million Dollars) for the rehabilitation of the
project, said the authority. enditem

