<HEADLINE> Netherlands to Crack down Soccer Gang Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Dutch government has announced
new measures to crack down soccer violence after a clash
between rival fans left one dead and many injured, officials said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Justice, interior and sports ministries, soccer clubs and
regional police chiefs have joined forces and proposed measures
aimed at controlling hooligans who organize gang fights using the
Internet and mobile phones to avoid police.
</P>
<P>
Authorities plan to arrest trouble makers and intensify
coordination among law enforcement groups nationwide.
</P>
<P>
No new laws will be adopted, but authorities will maximize
existing laws, such as tough powers to deal with organized crime
gangs, to make it easier to arrest hooligans before they cause
trouble.
</P>
<P>
Authorities also plan to register vandalism incidents and
exchange records on known hooligans. 
</P>
