<HEADLINE> 5 Killed When Clan Fighting Erupts in C. Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 3 (Xinhua) -- At least five people were
killed and eight others wounded when clan fighting broke out
between militiamen from Hawadle and Galjel clans at Burane
village, 113 kilometers north of Mogadishu on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said about 10 armed wagons were used in
the battle and the road linking the capital with the central
region of the country has been disrupted.
</P>
<P>
Commuters who arrived here today said the clashes were
provoked by the killing of a man and the theft of a lorry near
the village, but both sides denied their militiamen were involved
in the job.
</P>
<P>
Reports from field radios said sporadic shootings could still
be heard at the western side of the tarmac road which divides the
two nomadic clans and in parts of middle Shabelle regions.
Galjel men had retreated as they were less armed, said a report.
</P>
<P>
Moslem elders from Galjel clan have appealed to their
counterpart Sheikhs in Hawadle community to help stop the
fighting, and peace efforts are reportedly on in the area
although no cease-fire has been declared so far.  
</P>
</TEXT>
