<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the North Lantau
Expressway, the first expressway constructed on Lantau, Hong
Kong's largest Island, was completed here today.
</P>
<P>
The 12.5-kilometer highway will be an essential link between
the urban areas and the new airport and Tung Chung New Town.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a ceremony to mark the completion of the work, H.S.
Kwong, secretary for Works, said that the North Lantau Expressway
demonstrated the accomplishment of highway construction in Hong
Kong through the hard work of all those involved in the project.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hong Kong had seen its most important changes in
infrastructure development during the past few years.
</P>
<P>
"As many projects are coming to fruition, the time has now come
to reap the harvest. The West Kowloon Expressway, Kwai Chung
Viaduct, Rambler Channel Bridge and Cheung Ching Tunnel have been
completed recently and some have already been opened to traffic.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Western Harbor Crossing and the Lantau Link
will also be completed later this month, adding that by May 22 the
balance of the above highways will be open to traffic.
</P>
<P>
He said that various activities had been organized to
commemorate the completion of the road link to the airport,
including an opening ceremony of the Lantau Link on April 27, an
international marathon and 10-kilometer run on the Lantau Link and
the North Lantau Expressway on May 4 and the Community Chest's
Walk for a Million on the Lantau Link on May 11.  
</P>
