<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ports of Entry of Guangdong and Hongkong to Cooperate more Closely </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Shared information through the
Internet and unified standards of commodity inspection are among
the achievements hoped-for between Guangdong Province's and
Hongkong's ports of entry.
</P>
<P>
A study on strengthening cooperation between the ports of entry
of the two places after Hongkong is turned over to the motherland
in July 1 is now under way.
</P>
<P>
"The objective is to create a more efficient port of entry
mechanism for the increasing trade and passenger flows of the two
localities", said a participant of a national ports of entry work
conference which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Under the principle of "one country, two systems", safeguarding
the national interests, and facilitating the flow of goods and
people, the plan calls for complying the work of the ports of
entry with international practices.
</P>
<P>
It suggests simplified procedures for cargo and more freedom of
passage for vehicles.
</P>
<P>
It proposes to use the Internet to share information on the
passenger and cargo flow, and the condition of vehicles.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong is one of the most developed regions of China and
the ports of entry linking it with neighboring Hongkong are of
great importance.
</P>
<P>
The Luohu Port of Entry in the Shenzhen Special Economic Zone,
for example, is China's largest passenger port of entry, while the
Huanggang Port of Entry, also in Shenzhen, is the largest cargo
outlet.
</P>
<P>
Experts say if the cooperation plan can be approved by the
Central Government and by the authorities of the two regions, it
can be realized in three stages, possibly between 1998 and
2005. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
