<HEADLINE> Beijing Firms Hold Symposium in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Eleven large and Medium-sized
companies from Beijing, China, held a symposium here today on
economic and technical cooperation with their Malaysian
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
The one-day symposium was organized by Beijing Municipal
Economic Foreign Relations and Trade Commission in collaboration
with Malaysia's Forerank Promotion and Exhibition Company Limited
with the aim to promote better understanding between the two
countries' enterprises.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 Malaysian entrepreneurs and businessmen
participated in the symposium.
</P>
<P>
Officiating at the seminar, Malaysian Minister of Housing and
Local Government Ting chew Peh said the event provided a good
chance for enterprises of the two countries to tap potentials for
increased cooperation on the basis of mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Yi Xiqun, assistant to the Beijing mayor and director of
Beijing Municipal Foreign Economic Relations and Trade Commission,
briefed the participants on Beijing's economic and technical
cooperation, hoping the event could help open up the prospects of
international economic and technical cooperation between the
Chinese and Malaysian enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He said that by the end of 1996, Beijing had achieved a total
value of 3.454 billion U.S. dollars for foreign contracted
projects and labor services cooperation and had fulfilled the
turnover of 1.583 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Over 25,000 workers were sent to nearly 100 countries and
regions to work in the fields of construction, building materials,
engineering, designing, machinery, electronics, metallurgy, power
supply, water conservancy, textile, agricultural production and
resources development, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing firms represented at the symposium included China
Beijing Corporation for International Economic Cooperation,
Beijing Municipal Engineering Corp., Beijing Residential
Development and Construction (Group) Corp., Beijing Urban
Construction (Group) Corp., Beijing General Municipal engineering
Design and Research, China Shou Gang Group Corp. and Stone
International Economic Technical Corporation.  
</P>
