<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Mainland Becomes largest Investor in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Investment from the Chinese mainland
has grown to the largest among the overseas' in Macao.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 companies have been set up in Macao so far with a
total of assets from the mainland valued at 90 billion patacas,
said Zhang Xuming, president of
the Macao Association of Mainland-Invested Enterprises, on
Wednesday night at the fifth anniversary of the association.
</P>
<P>
Firms established with capital from the mainland deal with a
wide-range of business, including trade, manufacturing, finance,
insurance, tourism, catering, transportation and real estate, the
president said.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the mainland-invested firms' business accounts for
half of Macao's finance and insurance, 50 to 70 percent of
tourism, 30 percent of import and export, and 70 percent of real
estate.
</P>
<P>
"As a matter of fact, the mainland has become the largest
investor among those from outside Macao," Zhang said. "(the
mainland's firms) have made a great contribution to the prosperity
of Macao and the reunification of the motherland."
</P>
<P>
The president said that the mainland's firms in Macao will
continue to do their part in the economic development and social
stability of Macao under Deng Xiaoping's idea of "one country, two
systems."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
