<HEADLINE> China Aviation Industry Show Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China Aviation Industry Show,
the biggest of its kind China has ever held overseas, was
officially opened here today at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Exhibits at the show include over 70 aircraft models,
aeroengines and civil products in real size and pictures, as well
as eight real aircraft including F-8II, F7MG, K8 jet trainer, Z9
helicopter, Y-12 multi-mission plane and FT7 senior trainer.
</P>
<P>
A few thousand Hong Kong people and tourists queued up early
this morning outside the exhibition hall to see the aircraft and
buy souvenirs of aeronautical characteristics issued at the hall.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Yuli, president of the Aviation Industries of China, said
at the opening ceremony that after decades' progress, China's
aviation industry has developed into a high-tech industrial system
with comprehensive disciplines and overall capabilities in
military and civil production, scientific research, education and
management.
</P>
<P>
He said that the industry has established economic and trade
ties with over 70 countries and regions around the world, and the
accumulated foreign trade value has reached 10 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The show will last seven days until April 9.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
