<HEADLINE> Thai Admiral Injured in Helicopter Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A helicopter belonging to the Thai
navy crashed this morning, seriously injuring a deputy
commander-in-chief of the Thai navy.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter developed an engine fault only one minute after
it took off at an airstrip in western Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter crashed when it was trying to land.
</P>
<P>
Adm. Suwatchai Kasemsuk, deputy commander-in-chief of the Thai
navy, had a leg broken and all 10 others aboard, mostly senior
naval officers, were also injured.
</P>
<P>
They were rushed to hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is still under investigation.
</P>
</TEXT>
