<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Song Jian: Poverty Eradication Not at Expense of Destroying Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- State Councillor Song Jian
stressed here today that the development-oriented alleviation of
poverty should not be at the expense of destroying resources and
causing environmental pollution.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech at the closing session of a three-day
national conference on aid-the-poor through spreading science and
technology, Song said the development-oriented aid to the poor
should stay in line with the principle of sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
Song, also Minister in charge of the State Science and
Technology Commission (SSTC), said development of the
poverty-stricken areas should focus on the rational and permanent
use of the resources and protecting the environment according to
law.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that for poverty-stricken areas to develop the
economy with outdated technology that consumes large amount of
resources offers no way out.
</P>
<P>
Song said that one major reason for an area's poverty is that
few people there know much about science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Song added that in the past few years, many scientific and
higher learning institutions made much efforts for aid-the-poor
work, saying it was a milestone for Chinese science and technology
circles.
</P>
<P>
The official called on more scientists and technicians to be
engaged in poverty alleviation work.
</P>
<P>
The State Science and Technology Commission today cited 457
scientists and technicians who have made outstanding achievements
in poverty eradication. Of those people, more than 300 won awards
of the Chun Hwa Foundation for Eradication of Poverty by Science
and Technology or Wang Yixi Foundation awards.
</P>
<P>
The Chun Hwa Foundation is jointly established by the SSTC,
Society of Hong Kong Scholars, K.C. Wang Foundation, EPSON
Foundation and Asia Agriculture Foundation in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yixi Foundation for Eradication of Poverty by Science and
Technology was established by Wang Yixi, former Director of
Qingdao Flour Machinery Plant.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the foundations are aimed at encouraging
more scientists and technicians to make contributions for China's
poverty alleviation.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, in the past 10 years, more than
800,000 Chinese scientists and technicians directly participated
in development-oriented aid-the-poor work and they spread nearly
one million items of applied technology in the poverty-stricken
areas.
</P>
<P>
China's poverty-stricken population has decreased from 250
million in 1978 to 58 million so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
