<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Bans Import of Zinc, Lead Ash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Delhi High Court ruled on
Wednesday that no zinc, lead ash and skimmings are allowed to
import from abroad, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The court gave the ruling after hearing a public interest
petition seeking a ban on the import of these "environmentally
hazardous" commodities.
</P>
<P>
During the hearing, the counsel for the petitioners contended
that it was the duty of the state to protect and improve the
environment and public health and provide pollution-free water,
air and environment for the people.
</P>
<P>
He pointed that toxic wastes like zinc and lead ash find their
way into the country from industrialized countries which perceived
this as a cheap way of getting rid of highly noxious wastes
prohibited by their own governments.
</P>
<P>
He said that zinc and lead ash are known to cause lung problems
and disorders of the respiratory tract and are also carcinogenic
(causing cancer) and because of their high solubility, leach
easily into ground water and soil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
