<HEADLINE> China's Zhejiang University Celebrates Centenary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang University, one of
China's best-known institutions of higher learning, today
celebrated the 100th anniversary of its founding.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng, and Chairman of
the National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee Qiao Shi
sent letters of congratulations for the event.
</P>
<P>
Over 40,000 people, including Vice-Premier Li Lanqing,
Vice-Chairman of the NPC Standing Committee Lu Jiaxi, and a group
of prominent academics from China and overseas attended today's
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Li spoke at the gathering, saying that the
university has been in the forefront in the country's higher
education and has developed its own characteristics and good
traditions over the past century.
</P>
<P>
The school has educated a large number of outstanding people
and has many achievements, he said, expressing the hope that the
university will provide new guidelines for the current reforms in
the field of higher education.
</P>
<P>
Pan Yunhe, president of the university, told the audience
that the centenary celebrations mark a new starting-point for the
school, for building it into a world-class university.
</P>
<P>
He said the university now has 11 institutes, 28 departments,
49 post-doctorate research facilities, and 23 labs and research
centers capable of world-class academic work. More than 100,000
students have graduated from the university in the past 100
years. 
</P>
