<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Leader Meets Norwegian Trade, Industry Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OSLO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese top legislator Qiao
Shi met here today with Norwegian Trade and Industry Minister
Grete Knudsen and the two discussed economic ties between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese
National People's Congress (NPC), said that China attaches great
importance to developing long-term and stable friendly cooperative
relations with Norway and is willing to enhance bilateral
cooperation in various fields, especially in economics, trade,
science and technology.
</P>
<P>
He said that Norway is a modern industrial country with
advantages in hydroelectric power, oil, shipbuilding,
transportation and communications, chemical industry and
environmental protection while China is a large developing country
with rich natural resources and a big market.
</P>
<P>
There is a great potential and bright future for further
development of cooperation between the two countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Knudsen, for her part, said that the economic ties between the
two countries have been very close, especially in recent years and
Norwegian businessmen are very interested in Chinese market and
are willing to invest there.
</P>
<P>
She indicated that Norway hopes that China will be admitted to
the World Trade Organization as early as possible and is willing
to make its own efforts to support China. 
