<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar lost a
quarter of a US cent after US and Japanese investors sold it on
the back of a softer gold price and concern about the short term
direction of the US dollar.
</P>
<P>
The local dollar ended at 78.19 US cents, down from 87.52 at
the previous local close.
</P>
<P>
Uncertainty about the US dollar's direction, another sharp fall
on Wall Street, a weaker gold price and a lack of local leads were
cited as factors contributing to the currency's fall.
</P>
<P>
Commonwealth Bank of Australia senior economist Tim Moloney
said the Australian dollar could fall to 76 US cents by end-May as
interest rates look less attractive and the federal budget looms.
</P>
<P>
On cross rates, the Australian dollar ended at 96.14 yen from
96.22 yen against the Japanese yen and at 1.3108 marks from 1.3117
marks against the Deutsche mark.  
</P>
</TEXT>
