<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Leader Meets Norwegian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OSLO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing
Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC), said here
today that China attaches great importance to developing its
relations with Norway.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Norwegian Prime Minister Thorbjoern
Jagland, Qiao said that Norway was one of the first Western
countries to establish diplomatic ties with China.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation and exchanges between the two countries in
various fields have developed rapidly for the past 40 years and
more since the two countries established diplomatic relations, he
added.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chinese President Jiang Zemin's state visit to
Norway last year has pushed the bilateral relations to a new level
and the Chinese government and people look forward to the visit to
China by Norwegian King Harald.
</P>
<P>
China and Norway are two different nations and they differ from
each other in some respects, he said, however, this cannot become
an obstacle to the development of friendly relations and
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries could witness the long-term and
stable friendly relations and cooperation through joint efforts
and based on the principles of mutual respect, seeking common
grounds while reserving differences, non-interference in each
other's internal affairs, equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Prime minister Jagland agreed with Qiao on the current status
of the relations between Norway and China, saying Qiao's visit
shows that the relations between the two countries in political,
economic, scientific and technological and cultural fields have
developed smoothly.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's rapid economic development has left a deep
impression on Norway and Norway is willing to strengthen its
economic and trade ties with China. 
</P>
