<HEADLINE> Colombo Share Market Continuously Gaining Ground </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Colombo share market is
continuously gaining ground since the beginning of this year,
according to sources for the Colombo Stock Exchange (CSE) today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the all share price index which began the
year by topping the 600 index point mark and ended the first week
at 603, rose from point-to-point and as at Wednesday this week
stood at 639.4.
</P>
<P>
The sensitive price index which began the year at 897 point had
increased by 80 points to 977 on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The sources noted that there was a strong demand for blue ship
shares and described the long-term market as being very
attractive.
</P>
<P>
The main reason for the strong improvement in the Colombo
bourse was due to corporate earnings in 1997 being above average
and beyond expectations of the business community, the sources
added.  
