<HEADLINE> Spokesman Reiterates China's Position on Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China hopes Israel will stop the
expansion of Jewish settlement in east Jerusalem and the Middle
East issue will be solved through political negotiations at an
early date, Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen Guofang told a
press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The increasing tension between Arab nations and Israel,
especially in the Palestine-Israel relations, Shen said, is mainly
caused by Israel's persistence in establishing Jewish settlement
in east Jerusalem, disregarding the opposition from the Arab
countries and the international community.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government is deeply concerned and worried about
this matter," the spokesman said, adding that Israel's position
and conduct have resulted in tensions and increased violence in
the region, and have brought the peace process into a difficult
situation.
</P>
<P>
Shen expressed the hope that the Middle East parties concerned
will abide by the relevant UN resolutions and act in accordance
with the principle of "land for peace" to seek a fair and
reasonable solution to the Middle East issue through political
negotiations at an early date.
</P>
<P>
China hopes the Israeli government will cancel the plan to
expand Jewish settlement in east Jerusalem, and try to create a
good environment for the continuous development of the Middle East
peace process, the spokesman reiterated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
