<HEADLINE> Share Prices Declines on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined in dull
trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index fell by 11.73 points to close at 2,078.08 points
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 137.26 million units, worth
315.96 million Singapore dollars (about 219.42 million Singapore
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 271 to 60, while 273
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
MBF Holdings was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 4.39 million units. It was followed by
the Hong Kong Land which had 4.28 million shares traded. The
Singapore Telecom was next with 3.64 million of its shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Prime Fund led the gainers of the day as it rose by 60
cents to finish at 10.7 U.S. dollars. The United Overseas Bank
(UOB) Foreign gained 40 cents to close at 15.5 Singapore dollars,
while the Overseas Union Bank (OUB) Foreign ended 30 cents higher
at 10.7 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Rashid Hussain was the biggest loser of the
day as it declined by 50 cents to 10.6 Singapore dollars. Gentings
fell by 45 cents to finish at 9.2 dollars, while the South Bank
Foreign A lost 44 cents to close at 3.7 dollars.  
</P>
