<HEADLINE> mee040304hke - Jordan to Lift Export License Requirement for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, April 3 (Xinhua) - Jordan is to Lift export license
requirement for many Jordanian-made products on April 10 in a bid
to encourage exports, Jordan's news agency Petra reported today.
</P>
<P>
The move aims to boost exports of Jordanian domestically-made
products by removing bureaucratic hurdles for exports, Petra
quoted an official of the ministry of trade, industry and supply
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The products exempted from export license of the government
includes some agricultural products, fertilizers, garments and
textiles, pharmaceuticals and electrical appliances.
</P>
<P>
Essential foodstuff and some important products are not
exempted, such as wheat, sugar, rice, milk powder, olive oil,
spaghetti, gold and silver, which need prior permission
from the concerned authorities.
</P>
<P>
Leather, crude oil derivatives, gas, cement, ammonium nitrate
and phosphate are excluded. Only Factories and companies that
manufacture these products are allowed to export their own
products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
