<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China and South Africa are
discussing the establishment of diplomatic relations between the
two countries, said Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen
Guofang at a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said, since the end of last year, South African
President Nelson Mandela and the South African government have
expressed the hope to normalize the relations with China in line
with international norms.
</P>
<P>
He said South African Minister of Foreign Affairs Alfred Nzo
had recently stressed that South Africa will sever "diplomatic
ties" with Taiwan, and that it is an inevitable choice of the
South African government to establish all-round diplomatic
relations with China.
</P>
<P>
Shen said China appreciated and welcomed those remarks of the
South African leaders.
</P>
<P>
Shen said, discussions on the establishment of diplomatic
relations between the two countries are on the track. "We are
willing to work with South Africa to realize the normalization of
bilateral ties at an early date." he added. 
