<HEADLINE> Agriculture Institutes Playing Bigger Role in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Academy of Agricultural
Sciences in central China's Hunan Province has signed cooperation
agreements with 100 towns of 20 counties to increase the use of
agro-techniques and improved crop strains.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreements, the academy will transfer its 700
agricultural researching findings and 100 fine crop strains to
farmers.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the academy signed 54 technological cooperation
agreements with 34 units, generating four billion yuan (nearly 500
million US dollars) in production output.
</P>
<P>
The academy has 13 research institutes and large numbers of
researchers. To date, 280 research findings by the researchers
have won prizes from provincial and central authorities. 
</P>
