<HEADLINE> Motorola's Paging Joint Venture Operational in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Motorola Paging Products
Co. Ltd., US-based Motorola Corp.'s first joint venture in China
went into operation on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Richard Younts, executive president of Motorola Corp., said
that his company will transfer more technologies, accelerate the
localization of staff, and improve the local content ratio in
cooperation with Chinese partners.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, clinched between Motorola and Shanghai
Wireless Telecom Equipment Manufacture Co., is designed to produce
high-speed paging products with an annual capacity of 750,000
units.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said China's paging market witnessed sharp
expansion in recent years. Only the country's post and telecom
authorities offered paging services for more than 20 million
subscribers. An additional six to ten million users are expected
to apply for the paging services this year. In Shanghai, the post
and telecom authorities-run paging stations now have developed
900,000 users. Other paging stations have another 900,000 users.
</P>
<P>
Motorola is now one of the major foreign investors in
China. The company's accumulated investment since 1978 has
totalled 1.2 billion US dollars. The Motorola Electronic (China)
Ltd. had been among China's top ten foreign-funded enterprises in
terms of investment volume and foreign exchange earnings back in
1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
