<HEADLINE> Hangzhou to Build International Tea Cultural Exchange Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Work will start on April 10 on
the International Peace and Tea Cultural Exchange Center near
West Lake, a well-known scenic attraction in this capital of east
China's Zhejiang province.
</P>
<P>
The center is the second phase of the China Tea Museum and will
be located on the museum's north side.
</P>
<P>
It will have a total floor space of 3,000 sq m, and will have
three parts: an international conference hall that can hold 300
people, a reference materials center, and an international tea
exhibition hall.
