<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0830 GMT, April 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- A majority of Jewish Israelis support the
establishment of a Palestinian state, reported The Jerusalem Post
today quoting a Tel Aviv University survey.
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Mount Anak Krakatau in the Sunda Strait, Indonesia,
about 300 kilometers west of Jakarta, has been spewing volcanic
ash and rocks for the past few days, an official said.
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Albania's Socialist Party, the country's largest
opposition party, decided Wednesday to return to parliament which
it had boycotted since July last year.
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- The head of the European Union delegation to
strife-torn Albania said Wednesday he was optimistic about that
order would soon be restored in the country.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian State Duma announced Wednesday that it has
established an anti-NATO commission aiming to oppose NATO's
eastward expansion, according to Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
BUDAPEST -- The Hungarian government has refused to send troops
to join the U.N.-approved multinational force to protect relief
operations and help restore order in crisis-hit Albania.
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Albanian Prime Minister Bashkim Fino did not ask for
the 13,000 Albanian refugees in Italy to be allowed to stay
permanently when he met Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
OSLO -- Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) Chairman Qiao
Shi said Wednesday that China and Norway each have their own
economic advantages and there is a great potential for continued
development of cooperation. 
</P>
