<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment in East China City Improving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Overseas-backed enterprises in
Yantai, a coastal city in east China's Shandong Province, are
providing greater backing for economic development.
</P>
<P>
Construction of a Daewoo-backed joint automobile parts venture has
started, bringing the total number of multi-national companies
investing in Yantai to 32. The venture will be be completed at a
total cost of 1.2 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The city now has more than 160 foreign-funded enterprises with
investment of more than 10 million US dollars each. Nearly 85
percent of the enterprises are involved in hi-tech projects.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment has helped the city build a group of
leading industries such as electronics, machinery, chemicals,
textiles, automobiles, building materials, and pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
Nearly half of industrial profits in Yantai last year came from
local foreign-funded enterprises, which contributed two-thirds to
the city's total earnings from exports.
</P>
<P>
In addition, foreign investors have shown a growing interest in
funding local projects in agriculture, energy, transportation,
tourism, real estate, and development of marine resources.
</P>
<P>
Yantai now has more than 900 foreign-funded farms specializing
in production of vegetables, fruit, and aquatic products,
which earn 360 million US dollars from exports a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
