<HEADLINE> Overseas Banks Join Chinese Inter-bank Money Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi
has become the first overseas member to operate on China's
national inter-bank money market, with a lending of ten million
yuan Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Seven out of the eight overseas banks doing business in yuan
have been approved by the central bank's local branch to join the
Shanghai-based national inter-bank money center, according to a
local banking official.
</P>
<P>
"The joining of the overseas newcomers in the national money
center not just provide them with a reliable channel for funds,
but are also conducive to a further maturing of the market
itself," said the official.
</P>
<P>
The money market, which began trial operations in early 1996,
was formerly connected to 19 Chinese banks and 35 regional money
centers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
