<HEADLINE> Sanchez Vicario Advances in Family Circle Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Second seed and defending
champion Arantxa Sanchez Vicario advanced to the second round of
the Family Circle Cup women's tennis tournament with a
straight-set victory in Histon Head Island, South Carolina, on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Spaniard breezed to a 6-2, 6-2 win over Sarah Pitkowski of
France in her opening match after receiving a first-round bye.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez, who has not claimed a title since the Hamburg Open 11
months ago, will next face 13th-seeded South African Amanda
Coetzer.
</P>
<P>
Third seed Jana Novotna of Czech fought back from one set down
to beat Switzerland's Patty Schnyder 3-6, 7-5, 6-1 in another
second round match.
</P>
<P>
Fourth seed Monica Seles, in just her second tournament of the
year, played the only third round match Wednesday and advanced
with a 6-2, 7-6 win over Czech Adriana Gersi.
</P>
<P>
Seles, who reached the Lipton Championships final last week,
will take on the winner of Thursday's third-rounder between
seventh seed Anke Huber of Germany and ninth seed Iva Majoli of
Croatia.
</P>
<P>
Huber lost only two games to defeat American Lisa Raymond while
Majoli needed three sets to oust Romanian Ruxandra Dragomir 3-6,
6-4, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Sixth-seeded American Lindsay Davenport overwhelmed South
African Mariann de Swardt 6-2, 6-0 in another second round match,
and unseeded Jennifer Capriati crushed Japan's Ai Sugiyama to move
into the third round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
