The NZSE40 index ended 8 points higher at 2,226 with a turnover
of nearly 75 million NZ dollars (51 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares rose 5 cents to 656 cents, and continued their
dominance of the market turnover. They accounted for one third of
the total value of the transactions.
</P>
<P>
Among other leaders, Air New Zealand climbed 3c to 258c,
Brierley Investment remained unchanged at 131c, Carter Holt Harvey
edged up 1c to 307c and Fletcher Building gained 3c to 425c. Lion
Nathan was the only loser, dipping 1c to 346c.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 33 rises and 39 falls.  
