<HEADLINE> Zambian Vegetable Exports Bring in 9 Million US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Zambian vegetable exports earned
the country 8,858,738 US Dollars in 1996, over doubled the
previous year's 4,023,390 Dollars.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by the 1996 annual report of the Export
Board of Zambia (EBZ) that available here today.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Export Growers Association exported a total of 1,436
tons of vegetables in 1996 from a total production of 2,000 tons.
The association has a paid-up membership of 50, of whom 24 are
direct exporters for the 1996/97 season. There are also
independent vegetable producers such as for paprika.
</P>
<P>
The EBZ is positioning itself as a liaison between
horticulture growers and the market place in providing marketing
and price information as well as flight availability. 
</P>
