<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Auxiliary Services Support China's Three Gorges Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China has formed a meteorological
service network in the Three Gorges Dam construction area to
provide timely information on hydrology surveys, forecasts, and
meteorological data for the gigantic water control project on the
Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Three Gorges Project Development
Corporation explains that the area is disaster-prone in its
weather and the construction is in many areas, so it is of great
importance that timely and accurate forecasts be available.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the company has built seven water
level reporting stations, two hydrological stations, and one
meteorological observation station in the dam construction area.
</P>
<P>
The company also continues to add stations in the construction
area according to the speed of construction and analysis of
meteorological materials, and has installed 23 machines to monitor
weather in major construction sites.
</P>
<P>
Related departments have also made forecasts according to
demands of construction teams and offered round-the-clock
consultation service.
</P>
<P>
The official attributes the smooth work on the three Gorges
project partly to the high quality of the services by all
departments concerned, and notes that the project has already
survived thunderstorms and torrential rains since construction
work began. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
