<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Passport Snatchers on Loose in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A number of people in Zambia are
going around to snatch Zambian passports from people in public
places, wash them clean with chemicals and then re-sell to
unsuspecting nationals, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a press statement from chief passport and
citizenship officer Bartholemew Tilasi as saying that the
passports were being snatched from people in banks, on the
streets and buses and other public places.
</P>
<P>
Tilasi advised the public to pay for passports and travel
document application forms at the passport offices throughout the
country and not through third parties. Applicants must demand to
be issued with receipts on the spot for any payment made at the
passport offices.
</P>
<P>
He also advised all passport holders to secure their travel
documents.
</P>
<P>
It was reported earlier that Zambian passports were found on
sale in Zambia and South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
