<HEADLINE> East China's First Technology Library For Young People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A small library providing books on
technology for youth, sponsored by a group of young people, has
been set up in Suixi County, Huaibei City, in east China's Anhui
Province.
</P>
<P>
The library was described by Zhou Kaiyang, one of the sponsors,
as a means of spreading the study of technology among young
farmers, and of providing technological consultation and training.
</P>
<P>
To make full use of the 'book house', a readers' club was also
established. Members of the club can participate in club
activities for a fee of only ten yuan (1.2 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
"Less than a month after the 'book house' was established, we
have distributed more than 2,300 technological materials on crop
planting and have gotten more than 500 readers," said Zhou, who
notes that they have a collection of nearly 10,000 copies of more
than 800 books, with 1,500 copies donated by the Youth League of
the county. 
</P>
