<HEADLINE> Zairean Troops and Rebels Enter Western Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A combined forces of about 500
Ugandan rebels of the Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) and defeated
Zairean troops entered western Uganda, local newspaper "The
Crusader" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Citing a military intelligence source in Kampala, the report
said the combined forces headed last weekend for Kyabitondo
County in Kasese District, a former hideout of the rebels.
</P>
<P>
A security official confirmed the entry of the combined forces
but could not determine the number of the forces.
</P>
<P>
The Uganda army in the district also established camps in the
area on April 1.
</P>
<P>
The Zairean soldiers were said to be a part of unit defeated
by Banyamulenge rebels in Bukira, eastern Zaire. The ADF had a
big camp in Bukira.
</P>
<P>
This is the second reported case that defeated Zairean
soldiers joined Ugandan ADF rebels. On March 25, some 200
defeated Zairean soldiers joined ADF in western Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The ADF had some 1,000 soldiers in its ranks last November.
But the Ugandan army had annihilated its main forces later. ADF
remnants since then divided into some small groups scattered in
the west and south-west. 
</P>
</TEXT>
