<HEADLINE> HK to Send 51 Athletes to East Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is to send 51 athletes
to the Second East Asian Games slated for May 10-19 in Pusan,
South Korea.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Amateur Sports Federation and Olympic Committee
(ASF&AMP;OC) has come to a decision on the list which includes 28
males and 23 females for the Games.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong athletes are split for eight sports at the event
-- four for athletics, one for diving, 13 for swimming, eight for
Wushu, 10 for badminton, four for judo, four for gymnastics, five
for rowing and two for bowling.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ASF&AMP;OC had earlier dropped football from the
Games team, citing that the Hong Kong team was not good enough for
the event.
</P>
<P>
But the Hong Kong Football Association (HKFA) said that the
tough domestic schedule made Hong Kong's team's trip to South
Korea impossible.
</P>
<P>
"We discussed it with the ASF&AMP;OC and decided that we should set
our target on the Asian Games (next year in Bangkok, Thailand),"
said HKFA chairman Victor Hui Chun-fui on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The HKFA has decided not to dissolve the Hong Kong team after
its final World Cup qualifying match against South Korea on May 20
and Hui hoped the team's head coach Kwok Ka-ming stay with the
team for long-term training.
</P>
<P>
Kwok's contract expires after the match.
</P>
<P>
Most of the players in the team, except the older ones as they
would be too old, will kept for the Asian Games, Hui said. 
</P>
