<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Financial Crisis in Bulgaria Easing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria witnessed decreasing
inflation, stability of its foreign exchange rate and improvement
in the financial situation of its banks in past month.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian caretaker Minister of Finance Svetoslav Gavriski told
a press conference today he attributed the healthy development of
the country's macro-economy to the great efforts by the caretaker
government.
</P>
<P>
Taking advice from the International Monetary Fund, the
caretaker government asked the banks to work out and introduce
financial policies suitable to themselves, Gavriski said.
</P>
<P>
This led to the steady increase in the value of the Bulgarian
Lev against some main foreign currencies, he said, adding that
the financial crisis caused by the devaluation of Lev and high
inflation was now under control.
</P>
<P>
Figures from the caretaker Financial Ministry showed the
selling prices of some imported items were going down because of
the stable exchange rate between the Lev and certain foreign
currencies.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, prices of medicines and petrol had decreased by 50
percent and 10 percent respectively. Prices of meat and milk had
also lowered.
</P>
<P>
Since the banks adjusted their financial policies, the State
Bank of Bulgaria has bought 150 million U.S. dollars from the
foreign exchange market, increasing the country's foreign
currency reserves, the ministry noted.
</P>
<P>
The previous Bulgarian prime minister, Zhan Videnov, resigned at the
end of last year. Bulgarian President Petar Stoyanov appointed
Setfan Sofianski as caretaker prime minister and the tenure of the
caretaker government is three months.  
</P>
