<HEADLINE> Fourth Mexico-Spain Meeting Inaugurated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 2 Xinhua) -- The fourth Mexico-Spain meeting
was inaugurated here today to deal with matters of mutual interest
and to evaluate the situation of the cooperation between the two
countries, Mexico's Foreign Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
In a communique, the ministry pointed out that officials of the
two countries will talk about matters of political, economic,
commercial, financial, legal-consular, scientific-technological,
educational and cultural nature as well as war against drugs.
</P>
<P>
The participants will also review the projects now underway and
the perspectives of future collaborations between Mexico and
Spain, as well as other matters of common concern at the
hemispherical and international levels.
</P>
<P>
Both Mexico and Spain agreed that they should focus their
scientific-technological cooperation on exchanges of experts and
information and on strengthening the formation and training of
human resources.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which will conclude on Thursday, is a mechanism of
collaboration and consultation established by the General Treaty
of Cooperation and Friendship signed by both countries in January
1990.
</P>
<P>
Of all the members of the European Union, Spain was the biggest
importer of Mexican products in 1996, with a total of 922 million
U.S. dollars worth of goods and the fourth biggest exporter to
Mexico with 642 million dollars worth of Spanish merchandise.
</P>
<P>
Spain took 24.6 percent of Mexico's exports to the European
Union while Mexico purchased from Spain 10.3 percent of its total
procurement from EU member states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
