<HEADLINE> Road Deaths Hit 16,782 in Thailand in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Road accidents claimed lives of
16,782 people in Thailand last year, an average of two deaths
every hour, according to statistics by the Thai Public Health
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The male victims outnumbered the females by five to one and
more than 60 percent of accidents were related to drunk-driving,
the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, about 1.5 million people were brought to hospital
emergency units nationwide because of traffic accidents, including
208,883 in critical conditions, it said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also pointed out that road accidents caused
property damages worth 180,000 baht (7,200 US dollars) every hour
last year in the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
