<HEADLINE> Indo-Sri Lanka Joint Venture to Increase Milk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- An agreement on a joint venture
between the Sri Lanka government and the National Dairy
Development Board of India was signed here Wednesday, according to
trade ministry sources today.
</P>
<P>
The new venture is known as Kiriya Milk Industries Ltd., and
will be headed by Dr V. Kurian who was responsible for making
India the largest producer of milk in the world.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the venture was more than a joint venture
of commercial interest. Sri Lanka is going to benefit from the
vast experience and ability of Dr V. Kurian.
</P>
<P>
They said that the venture will bring about a significant
change in Sri Lanka's rural economy in which rural women will be
the main players.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka will increase milk production from 100,000 liters to
300,000 liters per day after the venture starts production.
</P>
<P>
At present only 20 percent of Sri Lanka's milk requirement is
produced locally.  
</P>
