<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Russian State Duma (Low House of
parliament) announced here today that it has established an
anti-NATO commission aiming to oppose NATO's eastward expansion,
according to Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
The newly-formed commission, which will work on the collection
and analysis of information about NATO's expansion, consists of 15
Duma members, including representatives of all political groups in
the Low House of the Russian Parliament.
</P>
<P>
The Interfax news agency said in a report that the commission
today issued a statement urging Russia people to hold a protest on
May 9, which marks Russia's victory of the anti-fascist war.
</P>
<P>
The statement also said NATO's expansion could threaten all the
Russian people of all political beliefs and that the protest will
be backed by all Russians.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that a protest against the NATO expansion,
organized by a parliamentary group, was staged here today.
</P>
<P>
The anti-NATO commission was founded in February this year,
with 240 legislators coming from different political groups in
parliament. 
