<HEADLINE> One More Section of Myanmar Union Road Put </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 3 (Xinhua) -- One more section of the
163-kilometer Lashio-Muse union road, which leads up to the
northern end of Myanmar linking China's Ruili in Yunnan province,
has been put into service, thus promoting the development of
Myanmar border areas and its border trade.
</P>
<P>
The 27.2-kilometer Hsenwi-Kutkai road, the second section of
the union road, was inaugurated on Wednesday after being upgraded
by the Asia World Co Ltd, a Myanmar private company.
</P>
<P>
The first section, which has a length of 44.8 kilometers
between Lashio and Hsenwi, was completed in January this year by
the same company.
</P>
<P>
The company contracted the construction of the union road last
July with the Myanmar Construction Ministry and the entire
Lashio-Muse union road is scheduled to be completed by the middle
of this year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Nawnghkio-Lashio section of the
Mandalay-Lashio-Muse union road is also being undertaken by
another Myanmar private company -- the Diamond Palace Co.
</P>
