<HEADLINE> Top Bankers to Stand Trial in Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 40 top public sector and
banking officials in Costa Rica, including the deputy transport
minister, have been indicted on charges of embezzlement and
prevarication, judicial authorities said today.
</P>
<P>
In one case, 15 senior officials of the Civil Aviation Divison,
including Deputy Transport Minister Jose Francisco Nicolas and the
CAD's former director Nelson Rodriguez, will be tried for
prevarication or breach of duty.
</P>
<P>
In another case, 24 former directors and officials of the
national bank, Banco Nacional, were charged with improperly
granting 700 million colons (about three million U.S. dollars) in
loans to "La Gilda", a rice trading company.
</P>
<P>
Two former managers, as well as former members of the bank's
board of directors have been charged with embezzlement.
</P>
<P>
A report by the General Auditor's Office of financial
institutions said technical errors were made, loans were
not backed by sufficient guarantees and other irregularities were
made in the granting of loans to the company. 
</P>
