<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Belgian Prime Minister Jean Luc
Dehaene arrived in Colonia, a city about 180 kilometers west of
this capital, tonight, to start a three-day visit to Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
His visit aims to re-evaluate the bilateral relations, review
the international agenda and analyze the role of the two countries
in their respective regional integration blocs.
</P>
<P>
