<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Moslem Community Supports Arab League's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's Moslem community fully
supports the Arab League's recent decision to freeze all its
activities designed to normalize ties with Israel as punishment
for the latter's action in building a new settlement in East
Jerusalem, a spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Lukman Harun, chairman of the Indonesian Committee for World's
Islamic Solidarity, said here Tuesday that the league's decision
was a correct answer to the Jewish state's arrogance in completely
ignoring the message of the world opinion that it should withdraw
from the territories it was occupying.
</P>
<P>
"It's been a long time since the United Nations issued its
resolutions calling on Israel to withdraw from the occupied
territories, including East Jerusalem, but the Jewish state kept
ignoring them," local press today quoted Harun as saying.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers of the Arab League on Monday wound up a
two-day meeting in Cairo with a call for a freeze on efforts at
normalizing ties with Israel to punish the Jewish state for
building a new settlement in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
According to Harun, the Israeli actions could be considered as
a proof that the Zionist nation was against peace.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
