<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's First University Association Of Non-Smokers Founded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The first non-smokers association
sponsored by college students was set up at Shanghai Medical
Sciences University in east China's Shanghai municipality recently.
</P>
<P>
The university, which was the first to prohibit smoking on
campus, last April, has established rules and regulations to ban
smoking on campus, such as banning cigarette sales on campus and
listing non-smoking as a basis for awards.
</P>
<P>
Only 17.38 percent of faculty members and 3.1 percent of the
students say they smoke at the university, in contrast to the
former 21.8 percent and 12.5 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The association has made a written proposal for college
students across the country and sponsored activities promoting
non-smoking.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, more than 80 percent of young men in
Shanghai spend from 10 to 20 percent of their salaries on
cigarettes. In China, 500,000 people die of smoking-related
ailments every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
