<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uruguay Beats Venezuela in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay defeated Venezuela
3-1 in a World Cup qualifying match here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay finished the game with 10 men after midfielder Paolo
Montero was sent off in the 76th minute for rough play.
</P>
<P>
Gonzalo de los Santos opened the scoring for Uruguay in the
30th and Paolo Montero made it 2-0 in the 47th.
</P>
<P>
Rafael Castellin pulled back a goal for the visitors in the
57th, but three minutes later Marcelo Otero scored the third to
seal the win for Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
The victory improved Uruguay to 4-1-4 and 13 points, only
behind Argentina and Bolivia on goal differences.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela, which dropped to 0-1-8, is last in the standings and
has practically no chance to qualify for the finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
