<HEADLINE> Central China Power Industry To Use More Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan province,
one of the country's major electric power producers, plans to use
10 billion yuan in foreign funds in the next five years for its
power industry.
</P>
<P>
Foreign funds are eventually expected to account for 30 percent
of the total investment in the sector in the province.
</P>
<P>
Seven projects have been approved by the province and
preparation for another eight is under way.
</P>
<P>
According to a high-ranking local official, the province will
give priority to power production rather than power sources.
</P>
<P>
The province has used approximately three billion US dollars in
foreign funds in its power development so far through 13
cooperation projects. In addition to the foreign funds, Henan
increased cooperation with domestic financiers, and it got 650
million yuan from commercial banks and companies last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
