<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Athlete Banned for Four Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Joao Luiz Do Rosario was
banned for four years by the Brizilian Athletics Confederation on
Wednesday for falsifying a time so he could compete in the Atlanta
Olympi Games last summer.
</P>
<P>
De Rosario, a 110 meters hurdler, lied about the time he ran in
the Chapel Hill meeting in North Carolina last May.
</P>
<P>
Do Rosario said he had run a time of 13.74 seconds, placing him
second on the Brazilian list for that year, but his deception was
discovered when the meet's organisers refused to confirm the time.
</P>
<P>
Roberto Gesta de Melo, President of the Brazilian Athletics
Confederation, said that though the suspension was equivalent to
those banned for steroids he considered the offence to be just as
serious.
</P>
<P>
He added that from now on only results forwarded by meeting
organisers would be accepted and not those relayed by the coaches
of the athletes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
