<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hill to Pull out of Michalczewski Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- WBA and IBF light heavyweight
champion Virgil Hill of the United States has had to withdraw from
his April 19 fight with WBO holder Dariusz Michalczewski of
Germany because of an injury suffered in training, it was
announced in Hamburg, Germany on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Fritz Sdunek, Michalczewski's trainer, said that the fight
would be rearranged for June 7 in the German town of Oberhausen.
</P>
<P>
Hill, who was to receive four million deutschmarks (2.5 million
U.S. dollars), beat Michalczewski's compatriot Henry Maske for the
IBF title in November.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Hill, a silver medallist at the 1984 Los
Angeles Olympics as a middleweight, has suffered only one defeat
in a 44 professional fight career.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Michalczewski has made nine successful defenses
of the title in his career haul of 33 victories. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
