<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Rocks Southern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 3 (Xinhua) - A strong earthquake measuring 5.5 on
the Richter scale jolted the southern Japanese island of Kyushu
early this morning, the meteorological agency said.
</P>
<P>
The quake occurred at about 4:33 a.m. (19:33 GMT Wednesday)
with the epicentre in the western part of Kagoshima prefecture,
according to an agency spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The quake was one of the aftershocks of the strong earthquake on
March 26, which registered 6.2 on the Richter scale, the spokesman
added. 
