<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IAAF to Give Green Light to Bailey-Johnson Duel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The International Amateur Athletic
Fedration (IAAF) are to sanction the 'world's fastest man' duel
between Canada's 100 meter world record holder Donovan Bailey and
the 200 meters world record holder Michael Johnson of the United
States.
</P>
<P>
According to Rolf Lund, President of the Canadian Athletics
Federation here on Wednesday, the IAAF's involvement would set the
seal on the 150 meters race, to be run in Toronto on June 1,
credibility.
</P>
<P>
"The IAAF's involvement will ensure the race has credibility
and integrity," Lund said.
</P>
<P>
Tickets, costing between 11 and 32 US dollars, are due to go on
sale on April 8.
</P>
<P>
Bailey, the world and Olympic 100 meters champion, and Johnson,
who took both the 200 and 400 gold medals in Atlanta last year,
will parade in the streets of Toronto three days before the race.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
