<HEADLINE> Macedonia Beats Ireland 3-2 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Macedonia beat the Republic of
Ireland 3-2 in a European World Cup group eight qualifying match
in Skopje, Macedonia, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ireland's Jason McAteer was dismissed for apparently striking
out at an opponent with his knee while Macedonia's two-goal hero
Mitko Stojkovski was sent off for retaliating.
</P>
<P>
The Irish had taken the lead in the eighth minute through
Alan McLoughlin but then gave away two penalties before
halftime.
</P>
<P>
McAteer and Terry Phelan were both judged to have handled
the ball in the penalty area and Stojkovski twice scored from
the spot.
</P>
<P>
They took a 3-1 lead in the 60th minute through Goce Hristov
and, Irish substitute David Kelly pulled a goal back in the 78th
minute. 
</P>
