<HEADLINE> Albanian Premier Asks Italy to Let Refugees Stay Longer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Bashkim Fino
did not ask for the 13,000 Albanian refugees in Italy to be
allowed to stay permanently when he met Italian Prime Minister
Romano Prodi today, said sources at Prodi's office.
</P>
<P>
He only requested the Italian government to consider extending
the temporary residence granted to the refugees until life in
Albania gets back to normal, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
Fino made a similar clarification for a talk show program
broadcast on Italian television Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Prodi's government has issued orders that the Albanian refugees
should only be allowed to stay for about two months at most.
</P>
<P>
Around 13,000 refugees have fled across the Adriatic to Italy
since unrest in Albania turned into rebellion last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
