<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest Chinese City Leases Old City Government Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Nanning, the capital of southwest
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, has leased its old
city government site to a Hong Kong company.
</P>
<P>
A special ceremony was held on March 28 for the transfer of
land use rights for the site the Canpex International Limited of
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The site is located in the downtown area and has an area of
14,028 sq m. According to a contract signed earlier between the
city government and the Hong Kong company, the city government
will lease the site and buildings at a price of 100 million yuan
for 50 years. In China, all land is state-owned.
</P>
<P>
According to an executive with the Nanning Canpex Land
Development Co. Ltd, which was registered by the Hong Kong company
in Nanning, the company will build the old city government site
into new multi-purpose buildings and commercial facilities with a
floor space of 112,226 sq m,
</P>
<P>
The project will be completed in six years at a total cost of
600 million yuan, he said.
</P>
<P>
The city government of Nanning moved to a new site in the
city's Nanhu District on March 1 this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
