<HEADLINE> Ukaine Beats Northern Ireland in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine beat the visiting Northern
Ireland 2-1 in their World Cup group Nine qualifying match in Kiev
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Andriy Shevchenko, 21, snapped a tie in the 71st minute to give
Ukraine the win after he took a pass from behind and flicked the
ball around a charging Northern Ireland goalkeeper.
</P>
<P>
Vitaly Kosovsky opened the scoring in the third minute, taking
a pass after a free kick and drilling the ball into the right side
of the goal from about 15 meters out.
</P>
<P>
Northern Ireland levelled the score in the 15th minute when
West Ham's Iain Dowie guided a penalty kick into the lower left
corner after the ball touched Ukrainian Oleg Luzhniy's hand.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine, which beat Northern Ireland 1-0 in Belfast last August,
will next face Germany, away, on April 30. 
</P>
