<HEADLINE> Scotland Beats Austria in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Scotland scored a 2-0 victory over
Austria in a World Cup qualifying game in Glasgow, moving seven
points clear atop Group Four.
</P>
<P>
Blackburn striker Kevin Gallacher, who has fought back from two
broken legs and other long-term injuries, fired the Scots ahead in
the 24th minute and powered home a spectacular volley in the 77th.
