<HEADLINE> South China Boom in Electrical Appliance Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Electrical appliances have
become a big source of profit for Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Total sales of electrical appliances for the home reached 1.95
billion yuan in Guangzhou in the first two months of this year, up
25.2 percent from the same 1996 period, according to the municipal
statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
The rise is 8.6 percent more than the year-on-year increase for
the city's total retail sales.
</P>
<P>
Consumers are showing greater enthusiasm for higher-quality
brand-name products, especially big-screen TVs.
</P>
<P>
Dongshan Department Store sold 886 color TVs, 51 of which were
63-inch sets, while sales of color TVs at the Friendship Group
reached 7.8 million yuan, 1.3 times the first two months of last
year. Popular brands include TCL, Changhong, and Konka.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attribute the boom to improvements in Guangzhou's
living standard and greater exposure for domestic brand-name
products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
