<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan Builds More Tropical Island Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 3 (Xinhua) --With the recent approval of Dongfang
to become a city, this tropical island province of Hainan in south
China now has nine cities under its jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
Before China kicked off its reform and opening-up drive in
1979, Hainan, which was then a part of Guangdong Province, only
had Haikou as its city. When Hainan was approved to turn into a
provincial-level special economic zone in 1988, it set up two more
cities of Sanya and Tongshi.
</P>
<P>
The island province now has built nine cities, one economic
development zone of Yangpu and has ten counties.
</P>
<P>
The nine cities are rationally located, with Haikou in the
north and Sanya in the southern tip, and Qiongshan, Wenchang,
Qionghai, and Wanning cities in the east, Danzhou and Dongfang
cities, and the future city of heavy chemical industry --Yangpu
Economic Development Zone-- in the west, and Tongshi City built in
the central mountainous areas.
</P>
<P>
Cities on the eastern coast have given their priorities for
economic development to light industry, tourism, and
high-efficiency tropical agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Danzhou and Dongfang cities, as well as Yangpu Economic
Development Zone on the western coast, where port conditions are
advantageous and mineral resources are rich, focus their efforts
on construction of an industrial corridor and the development of
heavy chemical industrial projects, as well as high-efficiency
farming.
</P>
<P>
Haikou has concentrated its efforts on building itself into an
influential center of politics, economy and culture for Hainan,
while Sanya, dubbed as "oriental Hawaii", has been busy with
developing tourism, light industry, tropical agriculture, and
related processing service. The two cities have built their
respective airports and port facilities.
</P>
<P>
Hainan's progress in urbanization has been made in tandem with
rapid economic growth. The gross domestic product (GDP) of Hainan
was 6.6 times of that for 1987, one year before the island became
a province.
</P>
<P>
Over the past years, the province has made an actual use of 5.2
billion U.S. dollars of overseas funds and has witnessed big
increases in its investment for fixed assets of the whole
society.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
