<BODY>
<HEADLINE> University Presidents to Attend Beijing University Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Beijing University is planning on
inviting some 50 university presidents from various countries to
attend the ceremony marking the centenary of its founding next
year.
</P>
<P>
The presidents of Harvard, Stanford, Oxford, and Tokyo
University have accepted invitations, sources revealed here today.
</P>
<P>
The university's anniversary falls on May 4, the day the
historic "May 4 Movement" was held in 1919 to introduce science
and democracy to the country. Beijing University was the
birthplace of the movement, one of the earliest attempts to
modernize China.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1898, "Beida" (for 'Beijing Da Xue', 'Beijing
University' in Chinese) was the first state-run university in
Chinese history. The founding of this Western-style school by the
late Qing Dynasty (1640-1911) signaled the beginning of a modern
higher education and modern science in China.
</P>
<P>
University presidents will hold a roundtable to discuss the
development of higher education in the 21st century, during the
celebration, sources say. Experts will also focus on Sinology,
which is becoming popular as the Chinese economy grows.
</P>
<P>
Several Nobel prize winners will take part in the event, which
will feature seminars on physics, mathematics, chemistry, and the
environment.
</P>
<P>
Beida is the country's leading university in both the sciences
and liberal arts and has the country's most renowned scholars.
</P>
<P>
The university will hold a seminar on Marxism, for which the
campus was a major focal point in the 1920s. Many revolutionary
leaders, including Mao Zedong, had connections with the
university. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970403.0280 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing's Flower Industry Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The flower industry in the Chinese
capital produced 18.6 million stems of flowers in 1996, 5.7 times
the figure of 1995.
</P>
<P>
According to the Capital Urban Greening Committee, flower
planting acreage was about 2,000 hectares last year and had 38 million
plants, double the 1995 figure.
</P>
<P>
Some 96 million single stems of fresh flowers were sold in the
city last year, eight times the figure for 1991. Sales of fresh
flowers were worth 100 million yuan (about 12 million US dollars),
including 700,000 US dollars in exports.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, 157 flower research discoveries
received city-level accreditation, and 380 new kinds of flowers
were introduced, bringing the total number of kinds of flowers in
the city to more than 600.
</P>
<P>
Flower research institutes have also made progress in using
wild flowers, with 84 new kinds of wild flowers cultivated last year.
</P>
<P>
There are 256 florists and three large flower markets, which
cover a total floor space of 27,000 sq. meters, in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, flower consumption in Beijing has
increased dramatically, and experts say that it will increase by
30 percent annually over the next few years.
</P>
<P>
To keep up with the general trend, the city will focus on
market construction and spend more money on flower research.
</P>
<P>
The city will also pursue favorable policies for the flower
industry to help its development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970403.0281 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Beats Albania in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 2 (Xinhua) -- European champions Germany fought
back from a goal down to beat Albania 3-2 in a World Cup
qualifying game in Granada, Spain, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Substitute Ulf Kirsten came in late in the match and scored a
hat-trick in half and hour to help the German survive.
</P>
<P>
Albania missed an early penalty and then went ahead from a
second spot kick in the 61st minute through Bledar Kola.
</P>
<P>
Kirsten then scored in the 64th, 80th and 84th minutes before
Kola scored another penalty in the last minute.
</P>
<P>
Germany stands third in group nine behind Ukraine and Portugal,
but it has played two matches fewer than Portugal and one fewer
than Ukraine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
