<HEADLINE> Nigeria Completes Repairs of Endangered Dam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has recently completed the
repairs of the Tiga Dam in northern Kano State, the largest dam
in the country that almost collapsed last August due to serious
cracks.
</P>
<P>
The News Agency of Nigeria reported today that workers had
used 1,500 cubic meters of earth and 30 tipper loads of stones to
repair the dam on the Hadejia Jama'are River.
</P>
<P>
The report praised that the relevant authorities, by giving
the job to local engineers, have saved the country's foreign
exchange and reduced its over-dependence on foreign labor.
</P>
<P>
The dam was constructed in 1974.
</P>
<P>
In 1988, cracks on the embankment of the Bagauda Dam in Kano
State led to the collapse of the dam, causing huge losses of
lives and properties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
